<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 5:24AM EDT  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central
Buchanan County through 600 AM EDT...
At 523 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Big Rock, or near Grundy, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Grundy, Big Rock, Vansant and Roseann.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
